<doc id="337830" wikidata="Q1185205" url="?curid=337830" title="King Dao of Zhou">
<text>King Dao of Zhou (; died 520 BC), personal name Ji Meng, was a king of the Chinese Zhou dynasty.

Dao succeeded his father, King Jǐng. After a reign of less than a year, he was killed by his brother Prince Chao (朝). Following King Dao&#x27;s death, the throne passed to another of his brothers, King Jìng.

==Ancestry==
==See also==
* Family tree of ancient Chinese emperors



