<doc id="337971" wikidata="Q1157091" url="?curid=337971" title="King Kao of Zhou">
<text>King Kao of Zhou (), alternatively King Kaozhe of Zhou (周考哲王), personal name Ji Wei, was a king of the Zhou dynasty of China. He reigned from 440 BC to 426 BC.

King Kao&#x27;s father was King Zhending. King Kao was succeeded by his son, King Weilie.

==Family==
===Sons===
* Prince Wu (; d. 402 BC), ruled as King Weilie of Zhou from 425–402 BC

