<doc id="337978" wikidata="Q1185191" url="?curid=337978" title="King Weilie of Zhou">
<text>King Weilie of Zhou (), personal name Ji Wu, was a king of the Chinese Zhou dynasty.

His reign started in 425 BC, after his father King Kao had died, and lasted until his death in 402 BC.

During King Weilie&#x27;s reign, he created Han, Wei and Zhao as feudal states separate from Jin, to act as a buffer between his royal domain and Qin (nominally one of his subject states). 

King Weilie was succeeded by his son, King An.

==Family==
===Sons===
* Prince Jiao (; d. 376 BC), ruled as King An of Zhou from 401–376 BC

==Ancestry==
==See also==
Family tree of ancient Chinese emperors

